kerone_employee":true},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"security","actor_is_team_member":true,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":692906,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::Comment","message":"The interesting question to me is \"Does the fact that HackerOne requires an active session and knowledge of the user's login credentials (password and possibly TOTP code) to alter the 2FA settings square with the fact that you seemingly only need an active session to know what the 2FA settings will be?\" ","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2015-11-20T12:56:55.412Z","updated_at":"2015-11-20T12:56:55.412Z","actor":{"username":"danlec","cleared":false,"url":"/danlec","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/013/404/1fb35d139fbfcb566e2513ca6c92f2dfe6cde541_original.png/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"security","actor_is_team_member":false,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":693053,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::Comment","message":"The backup codes are generated (but *not* saved) every time you load the 2FA page. As in, reload the page, and you will get a different set of backup codes (until you actually enter your password and your TOTP code). With that in mind, is this really a concern in itself?","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2015-11-20T15:47:37.843Z","updated_at":"2015-11-20T15:47:37.843Z","actor":{"username":"reed","cleared":false,"url":"/reed","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/003/132/66d7eadcea16b878bb67bfd697b9542250a801a7_original.jpg/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"security","actor_is_team_member":false,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":693057,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::Comment","message":"@reed Interesting.  In my experimentation I wasn't (and still don't appear to be) getting a different set of backup codes on a reload.  On refresh I observe the various `authenticity_token`s changing, but the set of potential backup codes remains the same. \n\nFor example, from the console:\n\n```\n$.get('https://hackerone.com/settings/authentication/edit').then(function(html){ console.log($(html).find('#regenerate-backup-codes-authentication-modal li:first').text()) })\n37d4 f16d ad0e a6b2\n$.get('https://hackerone.com/settings/authentication/edit').then(function(html){ console.log($(html).find('#regenerate-backup-codes-authentication-modal li:first').text()) })\n37d4 f16d ad0e a6b2\n$.get('https://hackerone.com/settings/authentication/edit').then(function(html){ console.log($(html).find('#regenerate-backup-codes-authentication-modal li:first').text()) })\n37d4 f16d ad0e a6b2\n```\n\n(and then if I open another window, and go to the Authentication section and click \"Regenerate\", that is the first backup code listed and would presumably be a valid code were I to confirm the regeneration)\n\nI may be misinterpreting this; I would agree that if the backup codes are in fact changing on every load then this is definitely not a concern.","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2015-11-20T15:51:37.591Z","updated_at":"2015-11-20T16:02:19.126Z","actor":{"username":"danlec","cleared":false,"url":"/danlec","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/013/404/1fb35d139fbfcb566e2513ca6c92f2dfe6cde541_original.png/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"security","actor_is_team_member":false,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":693142,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::Comment","message":"I believe we generate a new pair and keep those ready in your session until you confirm these are the codes you want (by entering your password and a working 2FA code). \n\nI'd like to add to @reed's comment that as soon as you confirm the backup codes, we do not know the plaintext anymore. We store hashed versions of each backup codes to ensure only you have the plaintext and we're just able to verify you do. ","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2015-11-20T17:00:14.418Z","updated_at":"2015-11-20T17:00:14.418Z","actor":{"username":"michiel","cleared":true,"url":"/michiel","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/000/007/439427fb81f710e5e16246ede1828613d46bb79e_original.png/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":true},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"security","actor_is_team_member":true,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":693145,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::Comment","message":"Ugh, you're right. In my earlier testing before this went live, I definitely thought I tested that case, but seems like it's not doing the right thing. We definitely shouldn't do that. :(","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2015-11-20T17:01:47.980Z","updated_at":"2015-11-20T17:01:47.980Z","actor":{"username":"reed","cleared":false,"url":"/reed","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/003/132/66d7eadcea16b878bb67bfd697b9542250a801a7_original.jpg/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"security","actor_is_team_member":false,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":693152,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::Comment","message":"@reed Oh good, I glad I'm not just crazy :D\n\nThe fact that the codes weren't being regenerated every time felt wrong (and was the thing I was trying to allude to with the \"possibly closes and re-opens the window\" and \"could be mitigated by not generating the 2FA values until the user is trying to enable 2FA\" in my initial description)","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2015-11-20T17:05:10.947Z","updated_at":"2015-11-20T17:07:20.689Z","actor":{"username":"danlec","cleared":false,"url":"/danlec","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/000/013/404/1fb35d139fbfcb566e2513ca6c92f2dfe6cde541_original.png/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":false},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"security","actor_is_team_member":false,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":700963,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::Comment","message":"Hi @danlec \n\nWe deployed a fix for this issue. Can you confirm this has been fixed now?","automated_response":false,"created_at":"2015-11-27T16:10:35.800Z","updated_at":"2015-11-27T16:10:35.800Z","actor":{"username":"martijn","cleared":false,"url":"/martijn","profile_picture_urls":{"medium":"https://profile-photos.hackerone-user-content.com/variants/5sJxxikBF7fwfkWs531JPtef/fd4ecbe1e3e98c343c7717114485ace2f830f9253103d3cfa7502059868c516c"},"hackerone_triager":false,"hackerone_employee":true},"genius_execution_id":null,"team_handle":"security","actor_is_team_member":true,"actor_is_concealed_member":false},{"id":700977,"is_internal":false,"editable":false,"type":"Activities::Comment","message":"I can confirm that https://hackerone.com/settings/authentication/edit now contains new backup codes (and in cases where 2FA isn't set up, a new TOTP secret) every time it's loaded.  Now if an attacker were able to get a potential set of codes it wouldn't matter, because that wouldn't be the set used when the victim went to confirm regeneration of the codes.","autom